    <stitle>BRAKE COMPONENTS: This Service Manual Section should be used for reference only. For more current service
        information on all components go to the Bendix website from the ISIS Suppliers menu and refer to the Service
        Data Sheets. - PRESSURE PROTECTION VALVE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>PRESSURE PROTECTION VALVE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="1">
            <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
            <para>The pressure protection valve (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0400214">Figure 14</hotlnk>
                ) is designed to close off air supply to any air operated device as long as the air supply is below a
                specified rating.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0400214" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0400214" filename="../figg04/G0400214.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="208px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 14. Pressure Protection Valve</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The rating of the valve used in the FMVSS-121 air system is 65 to 75 psi.</para>
            <para>It is important that this valve be installed when any auxiliary attachments are installed on a vehicle
                to avoid complete loss of air in the event of an air leak in any of the air operated attachments.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
